Package ohos.agp.components.webengine

Class BrowserAgent

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.agp.components.webengine.BrowserAgent

  • public class BrowserAgent
extends Object
    Assists WebView in processing web content callbacks, for example, processing JavaScript events and website attribute change events.
    Since:
    5
    See Also:
    WebView.setBrowserAgent(ohos.agp.components.webengine.BrowserAgent)

      • onJsMessageShow

        public boolean onJsMessageShow​(WebView webView,
                               String url,
                               String message,
                               boolean isAlert,
                               JsMessageResult result)
        Called when the page receives a JavaScript message pop-up.
        Parameters:
        webView - Indicates the WebView that initiates the callback.
        url - Indicates the URL of the WebView.
        message - Indicates the message to be displayed in the pop-up.
        isAlert - Specifies whether the message is intended for alerting. true indicates an alert message, and false indicates a confirmation message.
        result - Indicates a JsMessageResult object used to respond to callback processing.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the application handles the callback result when the pop-up is confirmed or cancelled; returns false if the WebView uses the default handling.
        Since:
        5

      • onJsTextInput

        public boolean onJsTextInput​(WebView webView,
                             String url,
                             String message,
                             String defaultInput,
                             JsTextInputResult result)
        Called when the page receives a JavaScript text input pop-up.
        Parameters:
        webView - Indicates the WebView that initiates the callback.
        url - Indicates the URL of the WebView.
        message - Indicates the message to be displayed in the pop-up.
        defaultInput - Indicates the default content to be displayed in the pop-up.
        result - Indicates a JsTextInputResult object used to respond to callback processing.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the application handles the callback result when the pop-up is confirmed or cancelled; returns false if the WebView uses the default handling.

      • onPickFiles

        public boolean onPickFiles​(WebView webView,
                           AsyncCallback<Uri[]> urisCallback,
                           PickFilesParams params)
        Called when a file selection event is triggered.
        Parameters:
        webView - Indicates the WebView that initiates the callback.
        urisCallback - Indicates an AsyncCallback object to asynchronously return the list of files to be uploaded.
        params - Indicates the information about the files to be selected.
